Adam Arthur Scaife B.A. M.A. MSc PhD FRMetS FInstP (born 18 March 1970) is a British physicist, and head of long range prediction at the Met Office. He is also a Professor at Exeter University. Scaife carries out research into long range weather forecasting and computer modelling of the climate. Scaife has published over 100 peer reviewed studies on atmospheric dynamics, computer modelling and climate predictability and change and recently published popular science  and academic books on meteorology.
